HEADWORD: Chemung period
<hw>Che*mung" pe"ri*od</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>A
subdivision in the upper part of the Devonian system in America, so
named from the Chemung River, along which the rocks are well developed.
It includes the Portage and Chemung groups or epochs. See the Diagram
under <er>Geology</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

